cs.CL, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV 

This paper focuses on improving neural machine translation (NMT) by addressing the issue of rare words, specifically named entities (NE). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and machine learning. The paper also involves character-level sequence to sequence models, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper proposes a new method to improve alignment in the bilingual training corpus, which could be categorized under cs.LG (Learning). The use of NE translation and alignment modules also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques.
